Interface IUpperSemiLattice<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ITree<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Tree, UpperSemiLattice

    public interface IUpperSemiLattice<T>
    A partially ordered set which has a greatest lower bound for any nonempty subset.
    Author:
    Gael Tregouet

      • compare

        int compare(T elem1,
            T elem2)
        Parameters:
        elem1 - any element
        elem2 - any element
        Returns:
        -2 if elem1 and elem2 are uncomparable, -1 if elem1 is a strict lower bound of elem2, 0 if equals, 1 if elem1 is a struct upper bound of elem2

        Returns:

      • getRelationMap

        java.util.Map<T,java.util.Set<T>> getRelationMap()
        If y ∈ Y and x is mapped to Y, then xRy (with R as the partially ordered strict relation of the semilattice). The mapping here is non-reflexive : if xRy, then x ≠ y.
        Returns:
        the semilattice as a mapping from any element to its strict lower bounds
